Workgroups for Windows is a simple window-configuration persistence package.

== Features ==

* Saving window configurations
* Restoring window configurations
* Persisting window configurations between emacs sessions
* ido-mode integration
* Simplicity

== Download ==

It's located at http://github.com/tlh/workgroups.el

== Install ==

1. Put workgroups.el somewhere on your emacs load path

2. Add these lines to your .emacs file:

   (require 'workgroups)
   (add-hook 'after-init-hook 'workgroups-load-configs)

3. To change the file that window-configs are saved in:

   (setq workgroups-configs-file "/path/to/new/file")

== Commands and Suggested Bindings ==

See the comments in workgroups.el




